catcheR_step1QC() performs the first plasmid QC step before single-cell catching.
At this step, the heterogeneity of plasmid clones should be high
The function allows to identify whether some plasmids have barcode swaps or mutation events

```{r setup, include=FALSE}
knitr::opts_chunk$set(collapse = TRUE, comment = "#>", eval = FALSE)
```

# Purpose

`catcheR_step1QC()` performs the first QC step on plasmid/intermediate cloning sequencing data. It is useful before the final plasmid-library QC because it helps identify reliable clones and potential barcode-swap information.

# Required input files

The input `folder` should contain at least:

```text
scratch/step1/
  rc_barcodes_genes.csv
  expected_shRNA_names.csv
  plasmid_intermediate_R1.fastq.gz
```

Optionally, you can also provide a clone list file, for example:

```text
clones_of_interest.txt
```

# Run step1QC

```{r run-step1qc}
library(catcheR)

step1 <- catcheR_step1QC(
  folder         = "scratch/step1/",
  fastq.read1    = "plasmid_intermediate_R1.fastq.gz",
  output_dir     = "Output/",
  sample_name    = "CATCHER1",
  DIs            = 100,
  ratio          = 10,
  plot.threshold = 2000,
  clones         = NULL
)
```

# Arguments

- `folder`: directory containing the input files.
- `fastq.read1`: FASTQ R1 file name inside `folder`.
- `output_dir`: root output directory.
- `sample_name`: label used in the dated run folder.
- `DIs`: read-count threshold used to define reliable clones.
- `ratio`: ratio threshold used by the barcode-swap detection logic.
- `plot.threshold`: upper plotting threshold used by the original step1QC plotting logic.
- `clones`: optional clone list file name inside `folder`.

# Output folders

```text
Output/step1QC/YYMMDD_step1QC_CATCHER1/
  csv/
  plots/
  stats/
  R_objects/
  to_scratch/
```

The most important checkpoint file is copied to `to_scratch/`:

```text
reliable_clones_swaps_*.csv
```

This file can be used later by `catcheR_sortcatch()`.

# Work with the returned object in R

```{r inspect-step1qc}
names(step1)
step1$paths
step1$files

# Reload later
step1 <- readRDS("Output/step1QC/YYMMDD_step1QC_CATCHER1/R_objects/step1QC_result.rds")
```

# Restart from checkpoint

```bash
cp Output/step1QC/YYMMDD_step1QC_CATCHER1/to_scratch/* scratch/10X/
```

Then use the copied swap file in `catcheR_sortcatch()`.
